(Match 42)  21st March 1891  (British Championship)
WALES - SCOTLAND  3-4  (2-1)
Referee:   Charles Crump (England)
Crowd:     4.000, The Racecourse Ground, Wrexham
Goals:     0-1 Boyd (15), 1-1 Bowdler (22), 2-1 Owen (45), 2-2 Logan (50), 2-3 Buchanan (60), 
           3-3 Bowdler (n/a), 3-4 Boyd (80)
WALES:
James Trainer - Seth Powell, David Jones - Arthur Lea, Humphrey Jones [c], Charles Frederick
Parry - Joseph Davies, William Owen, William Haighton Turner, John Charles Henry Bowdler,
William Lewis.

SCOTLAND:
